        <num>CC 1867</num>
        <heading>1867.  Imputation by obligee</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 1867.  Imputation by obligee
An obligor who has accepted a receipt that imputes payment to one of his debts may no longer demand imputation to another debt, unless the obligee has acted in bad faith.</p>
        </content>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=109109</p>
